</ul>

<p><strong>2. The Rise of Anti-Vaping Sentiment and Public Perception:</strong></p>

<p>Negative public perception surrounding vaping, often fueled by concerns about youth vaping and misinformation, contributes to a challenging business environment. <strong>Anti-vaping sentiment</strong> can lead to decreased customer traffic, community resistance to new vape shop openings, and even increased scrutiny from landlords and local authorities. While RELX positions itself as a responsible brand focused on adult harm reduction, the broader negative narrative around vaping can still impact the entire industry.</p>

<p><strong>3. Economic Headwinds and Shifting Consumer Behavior:</strong></p>

<p>Beyond regulations, broader economic factors play a role. Like many small businesses, vape shops face rising operating costs, including rent, utilities, and inventory. Furthermore, consumer behavior is evolving. While brick-and-mortar stores were initially the primary channel for vape product purchases, <strong>online vape sales growth</strong> has become a significant trend. The convenience and often competitive pricing of online retailers present a challenge to traditional vape shops.</p>

